## Build

```bash
icp build --debug      # or: dfx build
```

| Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Motoko type or syntax error | Real compile error | Read the trap location; fix the type. Minimal edit only. |
| Import cannot be resolved | Broken mops dep or missing `mops install` | Re-run `mops install`; check `mops.toml` vs `mops.lock` for drift |
| `mops.lock` inconsistent | Lockfile stale, or dep added without install | Reinstall to regenerate; do not hand-edit |
| `.did` not generated | Candid gen failed silently after a compile error | Fix the compile error first — candid gen runs *after* a successful build |
| Rust: wasm target missing | `wasm32-unknown-unknown` not installed | `rustup target add wasm32-unknown-unknown` |

**Never debug a deploy failure while the build is broken.** A stale `.wasm` from a previous
successful build will happily deploy and then behave like the code you did not just write.

