## Runtime & canister logic

Symptoms: `ic0.trap`, reject codes, methods failing on a canister that deployed fine.

| Symptom | What it actually means | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| `Admin not set` | `init()` never ran, ran without the admin principal, or a **post-upgrade wiped it** because it was not stable | Set admin in `init()`; mark it `stable`; re-verify after upgrade |
| `Registry not set` | The **post-deploy wiring call was never made.** Deploying canisters does not connect them — that is a separate call. | Make the wiring call after deploy. Script it, or it will be forgotten every time. |
| `ic0.trap` on a method that worked before | State lost across upgrade — a non-`stable` var reset to default | Mark it `stable`, or restore in `postupgrade()` |
| `CanisterError` reject | Trap inside the callee; its trap message is the real error | Read the *callee's* logs, not the caller's |
| Access control fails for the right principal | Anonymous principal reaching the canister | See Frontend — identity not attached agent-side |

**Validate the initialization flow explicitly:**
- `init()` — runs **once**, on first install. Not on upgrade.
- `postupgrade()` — runs on upgrade. Anything not `stable` is **gone** by the time it runs.
- Stable variables — all state that must survive an upgrade must be `stable`. Source of most
  "it worked yesterday" bugs.
- Post-deploy wiring — admin setup, registry registration, inter-canister references.
  **These are not part of deploy.** If not scripted, not happening.

