## Candid & inter-canister

```bash
icp canister call <canister> <method> '(<args>)'
```
Also use the Candid UI to exercise methods independent of any frontend.

| Symptom | Likely cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| Method not found | `.did` is stale — caller using a pre-build `.did` | Regenerate `.did`, regenerate frontend declarations, rebuild frontend |
| Encoding/decoding error | Type mismatch between caller's `.did` and the actual signature | Diff the deployed `.did` against the one the caller uses |
| `opt` field arrives null | Optional-field encoding mismatch | Check exact `opt` nesting on both sides |
| Inter-canister call rejects | Callee trapped, or its interface changed without the caller rebuilt | Read the callee's trap, then rebuild both sides |

**The `.did` is the contract.** Verify it matches the *deployed* canister, not the local source tree.

